ARE GIVEN IN TEXT.
SURVEY OF RECENT EXPERIMENTS FOR
THE LI-7 SYSTEM REVIEWS THE PRESENT
WORK.

PRELIMINARY WORK.
3.75 MV VAN DE GRAAFF OF CBNM PROVIDED A PULSED
PROTON BEAM OF MEAN CURRENT ABOUT 4.5 MICROA,WITH A
PULSE WIDTH OF 1 NS AT 1MHZ REPITITION RATE.
.PROTON ENERGY IS KNOWN TO BETTER THAN 0.75 PC FROM
1.5 TO 3.75 MEV.ENERGY SPREAD OF THE BEAM IS +-1 KEV.
LEAST SQUARE FITS TO THE ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS
WITH A LEGENDRE POLYNOMIAL EXPANSION YIELDED THE
INTEGRATED ELASTIC NEUTRON SCATTERING CROSS SECTION
OF LI-6 AND THE LEGENDRE COEFFICIENTS B1 TO B4.
.A SIMULTANEOUS FIT TO THE TOTAL AND ANGLE INTEGRATED
SCT.CS. WAS MADE BY USING THE SINGLE LEVEL BREIT-
WIGNER FORMULA PLUS LINEAR BACKGROUND TERMS.THE
1/SQUARE ROOT(E) DEPENDENCE OF THE (N,T) CS. WAS
ALSO INCLUDED.
.THE LI-6(N,T)HE-4 CS. WAS CALCULATED BY MEANS OF THE
RELATION SIGMA(N,T)=SIGMA(TOT)-SIGMA(N,N),AND THE
UPPER AND LOWER LIMITS DETERMINED FROM THE ANALYTIC
PARAMETERS OF SIGMA(TOT) AND SIGMA(N,N) EXPRESSIONS.
.FOR TOT.CS.MEAS.,INSCATTERING,ISOTOPIC CONTENT OF
LI-7 IN THE SAMPLE,ELECTRONIC DEADTIME AND ENERGY
SPREAD (+-7.5KEV) OF THE INCIDENT NEUTRONS WERE
TAKEN INTO ACCOUNT.
.FOR SCT.CS.MEAS.,CORRECTIONS WERE APPLIED FOR THE
ATTENUATION OF THE INCIDENT NEUTRON BEAM IN BOTH LI
AND CH2 SAMPLES,FOR INSCATTERING AND MULTIPLE
SCATTERING,FOR REMOVAL.
.CURVES CORRESPONDING TO DATA GIVEN IN HERE PLUS
COMPARISON WITH OTHER PREVIOUS WORKS WERE PRESENTED.
NEUTRON TIME OF FLIGHT DETECTORS,PLACED IN A
LARGE COLLIMATING SHIELD,CONSISTED OF NE-224 LIQUID
SCINTILLATOR OF 5 CM DIAMETER AND 2.5 CM LENGTH VIEWED
DIRECTLY BY A LOW NOISE PHOTOMULTIPLIER OF RCA-8850
TYPE.NEUTRON THRESHOLD FOR THIS DETECTOR CORRESPONDED
TO 30KEV NEUTRON ENERGY.
.FOR TOT.CS.MEAS.,TWO DETECTORS,WERE POSITIONED AT A
DISTANCE OF 241 CM FROM THE NEUTRON PRODUCING TARGET,
ONE OF THEM AT 0 DEGREE WITH RESPECT TO THE PROTON
BEAM DIRECTION,THE OTHER AT 25 DEGREES AND USED TO
MONITOR THE NEUTRON FLUENCE.
.FOR SCT.CS.MEAS.,THREE DETECTORS COULD BE MOVED ON A
CIRCLE WITH THE SAMPLE AXIS AS THE CENTRE POINT,A
FOURTH ONE WAS USED TO MONITOR THE NEUTRON FLUENCE.
3.75 MV VAN DE GRAAFF OF CBNM PROVIDED A PULSED
PROTON BEAM OF MEAN CURRENT ABOUT 4.5 MICROA,WITH A
PULSE WIDTH OF 1 NS AT 1MHZ REPITITION RATE.
.PROTON ENERGY IS KNOWN TO BETTER THAN 0.75 PC FROM
1.5 TO 3.75 MEV.ENERGY SPREAD OF THE BEAM IS +-1 KEV.
.FOR TOTAL C.S. MEAS. LI-F TARGET OF 60 MICROG/CM2
THICKNESS GAVE NEUTRONS IN THE RANGE 80 KEV TO 1.4 MEV
AT 0 DEGREE WITH RESPECT TO THE PROTON DIRECTION.
.FOR SCT C.S. MEAS.,IN THE NEUTRON ENERGY RANGE 0.22 TO
0.35MEV AND 0.39 TO 0.95 MEV,LIF TARGETS OF 200 AND
235 MICROGRAMS/CM2 WERE USED RESPECTIVELY.
.FOR TOT.CS.MEAS.,TIT TARGET OF 200 MICROGRAMS/CM2
THICKNESS WAS USED IN THE NEUTRON RANGE 1.4 TO 3.MEV.
.FOR SCT.CS.MEAS.,TIT TARGET OF 390 MICROG/CM2
THICKNESS WAS EMPLOYED IN THE HIGHER ENERGY RANGE.
TRANSMISSION METHOD USING MONOENERGETIC NEUTRON
AND EMPLOYING THE FAST NEUTRON TIME OF FLIGHT
TECHNIQUE.TWO TIME OF FLIGHT SPECTRA,ONE FOR THE
SAMPLE,THE OTHER FOR THE EMPTY CAN WERE RECORDED FOR
A FILED NUMBER OF MONITOR COUNTS.
.FOR TOT.CS.MEAS.,FLIGHT PATH WAS 241+-0.5CM LONG.
.FOR SCT.CS.MEAS.,FLIGHT PATHES WERE 115 AND 145 CM
LONG FOR SAMPLES IV AND II RESPECTIVELY.
.SAMPLES WERE COMPOSED OF (95.63+-0.1)PC.LI-6,
TRACES SMALLER THAN 0.002 PC.
.THEY WERE ENCAPSULATED IN A 0.15 MM THICK AL CONTAINER
FIXED BY THIN AL RODS ON A SAMPLE CHANGER.
.THERE WERE FOUR CYLINDRICAL SAMPLES,SIZE OF WHICH
WERE RESPECTIVELY (DIAMETER AND LENGTH),IN MM,
.FOR TOT.CS.MEAS.,SAMPLES I,II,III WERE USED IN THE
ENERGY RANGES (0.08 TO 0.16 AND 0.4 TO 3.0)MEV,
RESPECTIVELY.THEIR AXIS WAS PARALLEL BETTER THAN 0.2
DEGREE TO THE LINE TARGET SPOT AND DETECTOR CENTRE.
EMPTY CANS OF SAME SIZE WERE USED.
.FOR SCT.CS.MEAS.,SAMPLES II AND IV WERE USED IN THE
RANGES (0.32 TO 3.0)MEV AND (0.22 TO 0.3)MEV RESPECT.
THREE CH2-SAMPLES OF 14.31+-0.06 PC HYDROGEN CONTENTS
WERE USED AS MONITOR,WITH RESPECTIVE SIZE(OUTER,INNER
DIAMETER,LENGTH) AND ENERGY APPLICATION,
.DATA AND COMMENTS ARE TAKEN FROM EUR-5726E.
